<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="162" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1192,1246]" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">
<taxonomicName authority="Viette, 1987" authorityName="Viette" authorityYear="1987" box="[151,469,1192,1216]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Negeta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="franeyae">
<emphasis box="[151,325,1192,1216]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">Negeta franeyae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Viette, P." box="[336,469,1192,1216]" pageId="15" pageNumber="162" pagination="82 - 89" refId="ref12315" refString="Viette, P. (1987) Noctuelles quadrifides de Madagascar nouvelles ou peu connues, XI (Lep. Noctuidae). Lambillionea, 87 (7 - 8), 82 - 89." type="journal article" year="1987">Viette, 1987</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:D82B87B5FFD9B151FF33FB86FCB9F967:555D6078FFD9B151FE41FB4DFDF1FB28" box="[485,620,1192,1216]" country="Madagascar" municipality="Zombitsy Special Forest Reserve" name="Lambillionea" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">Lambillionea</location>
87(7–8): 83. Type locality: 
<collectingCountry box="[935,1059,1192,1216]" name="Madagascar" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingMunicipality box="[1075,1432,1192,1216]" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">Zombitsy Special Forest Reserve</collectingMunicipality>
, Matsabory. 
<typeStatus box="[319,416,1222,1246]" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">Holotype</typeStatus>
, female (MNHN).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1292,1679]" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,348,1292,1319]" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">Taxonomic note.</emphasis>
In a recently published review of the Afrotropical 
<taxonomicName authority="Laszlo, Ronkay &amp; Witt, 2010" authorityName="Laszlo, Ronkay &amp; Witt" authorityYear="2010" box="[914,1383,1292,1319]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Leucobaeta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[914,1045,1292,1318]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">Leucobaeta</emphasis>
László, Ronkay &amp; Witt, 2010
</taxonomicName>
, two sister species of the distinctive West African species 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hampson, 1918)" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[750,1196,1328,1355]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Leucobaeta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semialba">
<emphasis box="[750,990,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">Leucobaeta semialba</emphasis>
(Hampson, 1918)
</taxonomicName>
were described from southeastern Africa and 
<collectingCountry box="[419,554,1364,1390]" name="Madagascar" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Laszlo, Gy. M." box="[568,711,1364,1391]" pageId="15" pageNumber="162" pagination="1" refId="ref12252" refString="Laszlo, Gy. M. (2022) On the taxonomy of Negeta semialba Hampson, 1918 with descriptions of two new Leucobaeta Laszlo, Ronkay &amp; Witt, 2010 species (Lepidoptera, Nolidae, Nolinae). Zootaxa, 5091 (1), 056 - 068. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 5091.1.2" type="journal article" year="2022">László 2022</bibRefCitation>
). The taxon 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[845,946,1364,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Leucobaeta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semialba">
<emphasis box="[845,946,1364,1390]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">semialba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally assigned to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Walker, 1862" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1862" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Negeta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1357,1436,1365,1390]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">Negeta</emphasis>
Walker, 1862
</taxonomicName>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Laszlo, Gy. M." box="[353,509,1400,1427]" pageId="15" pageNumber="162" pagination="1" refId="ref12252" refString="Laszlo, Gy. M. (2022) On the taxonomy of Negeta semialba Hampson, 1918 with descriptions of two new Leucobaeta Laszlo, Ronkay &amp; Witt, 2010 species (Lepidoptera, Nolidae, Nolinae). Zootaxa, 5091 (1), 056 - 068. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 5091.1.2" type="journal article" year="2022">László (2022)</bibRefCitation>
transferred the species to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laszlo, Ronkay &amp; Witt" authorityYear="2010" box="[798,929,1400,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Leucobaeta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[798,929,1400,1426]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">Leucobaeta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on morphological analysis. At the time of the preparation of the manuscript, the author was not aware of the existence of another similar “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1862" box="[1257,1336,1437,1462]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Negeta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1257,1336,1437,1462]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">Negeta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” species described from 
<collectingCountry box="[328,463,1472,1498]" name="Madagascar" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Viette, P." box="[507,659,1472,1499]" pageId="15" pageNumber="162" pagination="82 - 89" refId="ref12315" refString="Viette, P. (1987) Noctuelles quadrifides de Madagascar nouvelles ou peu connues, XI (Lep. Noctuidae). Lambillionea, 87 (7 - 8), 82 - 89." type="journal article" year="1987">Viette (1987)</bibRefCitation>
. Having compared the type series of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laszlo" authorityYear="2022" box="[1079,1230,1472,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Leucobaeta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malagassa">
<emphasis box="[1079,1230,1472,1498]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">L. malagassa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the image of the 
<typeStatus box="[192,290,1508,1534]" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viette" authorityYear="1987" box="[325,455,1509,1535]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Negeta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="franeyae">
<emphasis box="[325,455,1509,1535]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">N. franeyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="De Prins, J. &amp; De Prins, W." box="[505,786,1508,1535]" pageId="15" pageNumber="162" refId="ref11361" refString="De Prins, J. &amp; De Prins, W. (2022) Afromoths, online database of Afrotropical moth species (Lepidoptera). World Wide Web electronic publication. Available from: http: // www. afromoths. net (accessed 3 May 2022)" type="url" year="2022">de Prins &amp; de Prins 2022</bibRefCitation>
), it is clear that the two species are identical externally and as there is no reason to presume the presence of another cryptic taxon of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laszlo, Ronkay &amp; Witt" authorityYear="2010" box="[987,1118,1544,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Leucobaeta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[987,1118,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">Leucobaeta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1156,1293,1544,1570]" name="Madagascar" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Laszlo, 2022" authorityName="Laszlo" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Leucobaeta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malagassa" status="syn. n.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">Leucobaeta malagassa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Laszlo, Gy. M." box="[278,423,1580,1607]" pageId="15" pageNumber="162" pagination="1" refId="ref12252" refString="Laszlo, Gy. M. (2022) On the taxonomy of Negeta semialba Hampson, 1918 with descriptions of two new Leucobaeta Laszlo, Ronkay &amp; Witt, 2010 species (Lepidoptera, Nolidae, Nolinae). Zootaxa, 5091 (1), 056 - 068. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 5091.1.2" type="journal article" year="2022">László, 2022</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[430,508,1581,1607]" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[430,508,1581,1607]" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">syn. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is considered here a junior synonym of Viette’s taxon. Following the results of the morphological examination of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laszlo" authorityYear="2022" box="[506,658,1616,1642]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Leucobaeta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malagassa">
<emphasis box="[506,658,1616,1642]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">L. malagassa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Laszlo, Gy. M." box="[705,867,1616,1643]" pageId="15" pageNumber="162" pagination="1" refId="ref12252" refString="Laszlo, Gy. M. (2022) On the taxonomy of Negeta semialba Hampson, 1918 with descriptions of two new Leucobaeta Laszlo, Ronkay &amp; Witt, 2010 species (Lepidoptera, Nolidae, Nolinae). Zootaxa, 5091 (1), 056 - 068. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 5091.1.2" type="journal article" year="2022">László (2022)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viette" authorityYear="1987" box="[881,1068,1617,1643]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Negeta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="franeyae">
<emphasis box="[881,1068,1617,1643]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">Negeta franeyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is transferred here to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laszlo, Ronkay &amp; Witt" authorityYear="2010" box="[151,282,1652,1678]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Leucobaeta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,282,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">Leucobaeta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Viette, 1987)" authorityName="László" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Viette" baseAuthorityYear="1987" box="[297,695,1652,1679]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Leucobaeta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="franeyae" status="comb. n.">
<emphasis box="[297,532,1652,1679]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">Leucobaeta franeyae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Viette, P." box="[547,686,1652,1679]" pageId="15" pageNumber="162" pagination="82 - 89" refId="ref12315" refString="Viette, P. (1987) Noctuelles quadrifides de Madagascar nouvelles ou peu connues, XI (Lep. Noctuidae). Lambillionea, 87 (7 - 8), 82 - 89." type="journal article" year="1987">Viette, 1987</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[702,804,1653,1679]" pageId="15" pageNumber="162">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[702,804,1653,1679]" pageId="15" pageNumber="162" rank="species">comb. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
